  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CIVIL ENGINEER (BUILDING CONSTRUCTION)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Plan, coordinate, and oversee building construction activities on site</p></li><li><p>Review and interpret drawings, specifications, and contracts</p></li><li><p>Liaise with consultants, architects, subcontractors, and authorities</p></li><li><p>Supervise site works and ensure quality, safety, and productivity</p></li><li><p>Prepare project schedules, method statements, and work programs</p></li><li><p>Monitor progress and resolve technical or site issues</p></li><li><p>Conduct inspections and ensure works meet QA/QC standards</p></li><li><p>Prepare reports, progress claims, and variation orders</p></li><li><p>Enforce Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) requirements</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent (recognized by BCA)</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>2–10 years of relevant experience in building construction<br />(Residential, commercial, industrial, or mixed-use projects)</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Strong knowledge of RC structures, architectural & structural drawings</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Strong communication and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Good problem-solving and decision-making abilities</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and under tight deadlines</p></li><li><p>Leadership and team-management skills</p></li></ul>",
